    </td>
    <td align="center" valign="middle" style="border-bottom:solid thin" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Anti-adipogenesis</td>
    <td align="center" valign="middle" style="border-bottom:solid thin" rowspan="1" colspan="1">Bark (ethyl acetate extract)</td>
    <td align="left" valign="middle" style="border-bottom:solid thin" rowspan="1" colspan="1">
     <list list-type="bullet">
      <list-item>
       <p>Ethyl acetate extract of 
        <italic>O. indicum</italic> bark was found to be the most potent extract for inhibition of pancreatic lipase enzyme and adipogenesis in fat tissue compared to other five plant species namely: 
        <italic>Limonia acidissima</italic> Groff (Kapittha)
        <italic>, Cassia siamea</italic> Lam. (Kassod)
        <italic>, Swertia chirayita</italic> (Roxb.) Buch.-Ham. (Kiratatikta), 
        <italic>Carissa carandas</italic> Linn. (Karamarda) and 
        <italic>Capparis decidua</italic> (Forssk.) Edgew. (Karir).
       </p>
      </list-item>
     </list>
    </td>
    <td align="left" valign="middle" style="border-bottom:solid thin" rowspan="1" colspan="1">
