    </td>
    <td align="left" valign="middle" style="border-bottom:solid thin" rowspan="1" colspan="1">
     <list list-type="bullet">
      <list-item>
       <p>Topical application of different concentrations of 
        <italic>O. indicum</italic> extract resulted in a concentration dependent rise in wound contraction and reduce in mean wound healing time. It also increased the DNA and collagen syntheses in a dose dependent manner at all post wounding days and the greatest acceleration in DNA and collagen formation was observed for 10% 
        <italic>O. indicum</italic> extract. The study of molecular mechanisms revealed the suppression of NF-κB and COX-II in a dose dependent manner in the regenerating wound of mice with a maximum inhibition using 10% 
        <italic>O. indicum</italic> extract.
       </p>
      </list-item>
     </list>
